# Render.com — Environment variables (copy names into Dashboard → Environment)
#
# FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON
#   Paste the FULL contents of your Firebase service account JSON file
#   (Project settings → Service accounts → Generate new private key).
#   Must be the SAME project as the mobile app (e.g. volvoegyptapp).
#
#   Render works best with ONE LINE (minified JSON). Example to minify locally:
#     python -c "import json,sys; print(json.dumps(json.load(open('your-key.json')), separators=(',',':')))"
#
#   Then paste the single line as the value of FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON.
#
# Firebase Storage bucket (required for dashboard catalog uploads to Firebase).
# Must match Firebase Console → Storage and android/app/google-services.json "storage_bucket".
# Examples:  volvoegyptapp.firebasestorage.app   (default for new projects since Oct 2024)
#            myproject.appspot.com              (legacy)
# If unset, the server derives  <project_id>.firebasestorage.app  from the service account JSON.
